VThe Blue Divine, an album by pianist Anil Srinivas and Carnatic vocalist Sikkil Gurucharan, will be released today, (October 17), 6.30 p.m., at the Ballroom of Taj Connemara. This will be followed by a special piano-vocal performance of the duo in aid of Cancer Research and Relief Trust (CRRT), Chennai. This is the fourth album by the duo and is being funded by Microsoft, another first in recording circles. The musicians have travelled across the globe and have received a positive response to their style of music.The CRRT, formed by four oncologists, aims to provide affordable treatment to individuals afflicted by cancer.
